$lang['Third-party application authentication'] = 'Third-party application authentication';
$lang['TF-Help-Description'] = 'When 2FA is active, third-party applications that connect to your Piwigo will no longer be able to do so using just your username and password. Until they implement a API key-based authentication mechanism or implement 2FA directly, Piwigo has provided a workaround so that these applications can continue to function without needing to be updated. We find it pretty clever, don\'t you?';
$lang['TF-Help-Step1'] = 'In your profile, create a new API key. Name it after the application you want to connect. For example, “Piwigo mobile iOS”. Be sure to save the “secret” of your API key, as it will never be displayed again.';
